          "date": "2011-04-01 19:46:21.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)",
        "message": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)\n\nThis patch does a lot of fixes and cleanup:\n- grab an inode refcount by top cl_object, so that it can't go away\n- cl_object now can be purged by shrinker\n- change the way to create cl_object, now it will be created\n  in ll_file_open and ll_setattr_ost\n- cleanup the code by defining cl_object_kill\n\nFuture work:\n- now pages and locks are holding a refcount against cl_object, this causes\n  cl_objects can't be purged by shrinker if there exists pages and locks\n  for an object. This is very bad, it needs fixing.\n- lu_object cache algo. The current alogrithm is not good, it should be working\n  as the following:\n        * if the object is in use, don't put it into LRU list\n        * when the last reference of object is put, put it into LRU\n        * fairness of LRU - LRU is tightly coupled with hash in current\n          implementation, must fix.\n- lu_obj_hop_put needs revising.\n\nChange-Id: Ia6cd1a5105db9ae4aa5556999e7c95510463501e\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jay@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
